'''Illegal immigration in China''' is a major problem, particularly with [[North Korea]]n refugees and defectors fleeing their country.<ref>{{cite news|title= Illegal immigrants pour across border seeking work|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=|url= http://articles.latimes.com/2010/sep/19/business/la-fi-china-illegal-immigration-20100919|accessdate=2012-04-01}}</ref> The [[Chinese Government|Chinese government]] actively discourages this type of behavior out of fears that it may cause instability in the region and encourage more illegal immigration.<ref>{{cite news|title= Beijing Increases Detentions of Illegal North Korean Immigrants|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/21/world/beijing-increases-detentions-of-illegal-north-korean-immigrants.html|accessdate=2012-04-01}}</ref> The government has been criticized for its aggressive approach to illegal immigration.<ref>{{cite news|title= Beijing plans curbs on number of foreigners working in China |work=[[Daily Telegraph]]|date=|url= https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/7756638/Beijing-plans-curbs-on-number-of-foreigners-working-in-China.html|accessdate=2012-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= China's Immigration Problem|work=[[Forbes]]|date=|url= https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2010/0719/opinions-china-immigration-illegal-aliens-heads-up.html|accessdate=2012-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Illegal immigration from Vietnam surges in S China|work=[[China Daily]]|date=|url= http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2010-04/11/content_9713105.htm|accessdate=2012-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Hordes of illegal workers crossing China's borders |work=[[Global Times]]|date=|url= http://www.globaltimes.cn/china/society/2010-07/550401.html|accessdate=2012-04-01}}</ref>

[[China]] is building a security barrier along its border with [[North Korea]] to prevent the defectors or refugees from [[North Korea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jurist.law.pitt.edu/paperchase/2006/10/china-building-border-fence-facing.php |title=China building border fence facing North Korea |publisher=Jurist.law.pitt.edu |date=2006-10-17 |accessdate=2012-10-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120820005602/http://jurist.law.pitt.edu/paperchase/2006/10/china-building-border-fence-facing.php |archivedate=2012-08-20 |df= }}</ref> Also, many immigrants from [[Mongolia]] have tried to make it to China. There might be as many as 100,000 Africans and Arabs in [[Guangzhou]], mostly illegal overstayers.<ref>[http://uk.reuters.com/article/idUKTRE57K27U20090821?pageNumber=1&virtualBrandChannel=0 Out of Africa and into China, immigrants struggle]. Reuters UK. August 21, 2009.</ref> To encourage people to report foreigners living illegally in China, the police are giving a 100 yuan reward to whistleblowers whose information successfully leads to an expulsion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lifeofguangzhou.com/node_10/node_37/node_84/2010/08/18/128210399779463.shtml |title=Illegal Foreigners Cleared Away during Asian Games |publisher=Life of Guangzhou |date=2010-06-13 |accessdate=2012-10-23}}</ref>

